'''Yerry Fernando Mina González''' (born 23 September 1994) is a Colombian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Italian Serie A|Serie A]] club [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

Mina began his career at [[Deportivo Pasto]] before joining [[Independiente Santa Fe]] in 2014, where he won the [[Categoría Primera A]] in [[2014 Categoría Primera A season|2014]], the [[2015 Superliga Colombiana]], and the [[2015 Copa Sudamericana]]. During the latter, he was named [[Copa Sudamericana#Awards|Young Player of the Year]] and included in the [[Copa Sudamericana#Awards|Team of the Year]]. In 2016, he transferred to [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], winning the [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] in [[2016 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|2016]] and being voted Best Centre Back in Brazil, as well as earning selection to the [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A Team of the Year]], the South American Team of the Year, and the [[Campeonato Paulista]] Team of the Year in 2017. He joined [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2018, winning [[La Liga]] and the [[Copa del Rey]] in the [[2017–18 La Liga|2017–18 season]], before moving later that year to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] in the [[Premier League]], where he spent five seasons. After a brief spell at [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] in 2023, he signed for [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] in 2024.

At international level, Mina represented the [[Colombia national under-23 football team|Colombia U23]] before making his senior debut for the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] in 2016. He has earned over 50 caps and scored multiple goals as a centre-back, appearing at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] where he was included in the [[FIFA World Cup#Awards|FIFA World Cup Fantasy Team]]. Mina shares the record for most goals scored in a single World Cup by a defender.<ref name="threegoals">{{cite news |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/news/2018-2019/yerry-mina-world-cup-sensation-in-russia |title=Yerry Mina, sensation in Russia |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=3 July 2018 |access-date=4 July 2018}}</ref> He also featured in [[2016 Copa América Centenario|2016]], [[2019 Copa América|2019]], and [[2024 Copa América|2024]] where Colombia finished as runners-up in the United States.

==Club career==
===Deportivo Pasto===
Born in [[Guachené]], Mina was a [[Deportivo Pasto]] youth graduate, joining the side only at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://independientesantafe.com/2013/12/yo-siempre-habia-sonado-estar-en-santa-fe-yerry-mina/ |title="Yo siempre había soñado estar en Santa Fe" Yerry Mina |trans-title="I always have dreamt of being at Santa Fe" Yerry Mina |publisher=Independiente Santa Fe |language=es |date=18 December 2013 |access-date=14 January 2018 |archive-date=20 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920055305/http://independientesantafe.com/2013/12/yo-siempre-habia-sonado-estar-en-santa-fe-yerry-mina/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Promoted to the main squad during the 2013 season, he made his senior debut on 20 March of that year by starting in a 1–0 away loss against [[Atlético Cali|Dépor]] in the year's [[Copa Colombia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hsbnoticias.com/deportivo-pasto-sigue-tercero-en-copa-colombia-33903 |title=Deportivo Pasto sigue tercero en Copa Colombia |trans-title=Deportivo Pasto remain third in the Copa Colombia |publisher=HSB Noticias |language=es |date=21 March 2013 |access-date=14 January 2018 |archive-date=14 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114183719/http://hsbnoticias.com/deportivo-pasto-sigue-tercero-en-copa-colombia-33903 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Mina made his [[Categoría Primera A]] debut on 15 September 2013, starting in a 0–0 draw at [[Deportivo Cali]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elpais.com.co/deportes/deportivo-cali-no-brillo-en-palmaseca-y-empato-con-el-pasto.html |title=Deportivo Cali no brilló en Palmaseca y empató con el Pasto|trans-title=Deportivo Cali did not shine at the Palmaseca and drew with Pasto |publisher=[[El País (Cali)|El País]] |language=es |date=15 September 2013|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref> His first professional goal occurred on 18 October, as he scored his team's first in a 2–2 home draw against [[Atlético Huila]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.minuto30.com/liga-postobon-pasto-aplazo-su-clasificacion-a-cuadrangulares-empato-ante-huila-en-casa/195265/ |title=Liga Postobón: Pasto aplazó su clasificación a cuadrangulares empató ante Huila en casa|trans-title=Liga Postobón: Pasto delayed his qualification to the quadrangular drawing with Huila at home |publisher=Minuto 30 |language=es |date=19 October 2013|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref>

===Independiente Santa Fe===
On 14 December 2013, Mina moved to fellow top-tier club [[Independiente Santa Fe]], initially on a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://independientesantafe.co/2013/12/santa-fe-confirma-nuevo-defensa-central-para-2014/ |title=Santa Fe confirma nuevo defensa central para 2014 |trans-title=Santa Fe confirm new central defender for 2014 |publisher=Independiente Santa Fe |language=es |date=14 December 2013 |access-date=14 January 2018 |archive-date=17 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150817122230/http://independientesantafe.co/2013/12/santa-fe-confirma-nuevo-defensa-central-para-2014/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Mina made his debut for the club the following 25 January, playing the full 90 minutes in a 3–0 home win against [[Rionegro Águilas|Rionegro]].

He proved to be a vital piece in the successful era enjoyed by the club, both domestically and internationally. In his first full year, he was part of the team that won the Colombian league [[Categoría Primera A]] Finalización 2014, defeating [[Independiente Medellín]] in the Final.

Mina then contributed to the [[2015 Superliga Colombiana]] victory by netting the first goal in the 2–0 win against [[Atlético Nacional]] in the second leg of the Finals.

Mina was a regular starter during his tenure at Santa Fe, which culminated in the 2015 championship winning [[2015 Copa Sudamericana|Copa Sudamericana]] campaign.

===Palmeiras===
[[File:Yerry-mina-palmeiras-nov2016.png|thumb|150px|left|Mina during a match with [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] in 2016]]
On 1 May 2016, Mina was confirmed as the new player of [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], but only joined the club in the following month.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/palmeiras/noticia/2016/05/palmeiras-acerta-contratacao-do-zagueiro-yerry-mina-do-santa-fe.html |title=Palmeiras acerta contratação do zagueiro Yerry Mina, do Santa Fe|trans-title=Palmeiras sign stopper Yerry Mina, from Santa Fe |publisher=[[Globo Esporte]] |language=pt |date=1 May 2016|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref> He signed a five-year contract with the club eleven days later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.palmeiras.com.br/news/2017/03/07/mina-firma-vinculo-por-cinco-anos-e-se-encanta-com-o-allianz-parque.shtml |title=Mina firma vínculo por cinco anos e se encanta com o Allianz Parque |trans-title=Mina signs five-year link and is delighted with Allianz Parque |publisher=SE Palmeiras |language=pt |date=11 May 2016 |access-date=14 January 2018 |archive-date=22 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190922184730/http://www.palmeiras.com.br/news/2017/03/07/mina-firma-vinculo-por-cinco-anos-e-se-encanta-com-o-allianz-parque.shtml |url-status=dead }}</ref>
[[File:BARCELONA-PALMEIRAS - 35587814492.jpg|thumb|upright|Mina in action during a [[2017 Copa Libertadores]] Round of 16 fixture against [[Barcelona S.C.]]]]
Mina made his debut for the club on 4 July 2016, playing a full game in a 3–1 away defeat of [[Sport Club do Recife|Sport Recife]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/campeonatos/brasileiro/serie-a/ultimas-noticias/2016/07/04/sport-x-palmeiras.htm |title=Com Jesus decisivo, Palmeiras bate Sport e mantém vantagem na liderança|trans-title=With decisive Jesus, Palmeiras defeat Sport and maintain advantage on the leadership |publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL Esporte]] |language=pt |date=4 July 2016|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref> His first goal for the ''Verdão'' arrived in the following fixture, a 1–1 draw against [[Santos FC|Santos]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com.br/noticia/613069_palmeiras-sofre-empate-do-santos-e-tropeca-pela-1-vez-em-casa-no-brasileiro |title=Palmeiras sofre empate do Santos e tropeça pela 1ª vez em casa no Brasileiro |trans-title=Palmeiras suffer draw with Santos and slip for the first time at home in the Brasileiro |publisher=[[ESPN Brasil]] |language=pt |date=12 July 2016 |access-date=14 January 2018 |archive-date=7 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207065023/http://www.espn.com.br/noticia/613069_palmeiras-sofre-empate-do-santos-e-tropeca-pela-1-vez-em-casa-no-brasileiro |url-status=dead }}</ref> He was, however, rotated off just before the end of the first half due to an apparent injury.  He was carried off the field on a stretcher, in tears. On 13 July it was confirmed that Mina would not recover in time for the [[2016 Summer Olympics]], with the recuperation from his injury expected to take six to eight weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lance.com.br/palmeiras/com-lesao-mina-fica-fora-por-ate-dois-meses-vai-perder-olimpiada.html |title=Com lesão, Mina fica fora por até dois meses e vai perder a Olimpíada|trans-title=With injury, Mina stays out for until two months and will miss the Olympics |publisher=[[Lance!]] |language=pt |date=13 July 2016|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref>

By late August 2016, Mina had fully recovered from his injury, and was an undisputed starter during the latter stages of [[2016 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|the season]]. In September, he scored goals against rivals [[São Paulo FC|São Paulo]] and [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]], and finished the year with four league goals as his team was awarded the trophy for the first time in 22 years.

===Barcelona===
On 11 January 2018, [[FC Barcelona]] and Palmeiras reached an agreement regarding the transfer of Yerry Mina for the remainder of the current season and five more seasons, until 30 June 2023. This made him the first-ever Colombian to play for the club. The cost of the transfer was €11.8&nbsp;million, and his release clause was set at €100&nbsp;million.<ref>Barcelona.com on 8 February 2018, Yerry Mina made his debut for Barcelona as a substitute in the 82nd minute in a 2–0 win over Valencia Cf in the copa del rey.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/news/2017-2018/agreement-for-the-transfer-of-yerry-mina-palmeiras-fc-barcelona |title=Agreement for the transfer of Yerry Mina {{!}} FC Barcelona|website=FC Barcelona|language=en-US|access-date=11 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona Profile |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/staff/players/2017-2018/yerry-mina}}</ref>

Mina made his debut replacing [[Gerard Piqué]] in the 83rd minute of the Copa del Rey semi-final against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]]. Barcelona would go on to win the match 2–0 and advance to the [[2018 Copa del Rey Final|final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2018/02/09/5a7cd77ee5fdea33778b457d.html |title=Copa del Rey – Valencia 0–2 Barcelona: Yerry Mina makes his Barcelona debut – MARCA in English |date=8 February 2018 }}</ref> He would make his home and league debut against [[Getafe CF|Getafe]], starting and playing the full game to a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/barcelona-player-ratings-yerry-minas-12008685 |title=Barcelona player ratings from draw with Getafe |first=Rik |last=Sharma |website=[[Daily Mirror]] |date=11 February 2018 }}</ref> He made his first official contribution at the club as he assisted [[Ousmane Dembélé]] in a 5–1 win against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=490378 |title=Barcelona vs. Villarreal – Football Match Summary – May 9, 2018 – ESPN |website=ESPN.com|access-date=7 June 2018}}</ref>

===Everton===
On 8 August 2018, Mina signed with English [[Premier League]] side [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] in a deal worth €30 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en-my/amp/news/barcelona-confirm-30m-yerry-mina-deal-with-everton/kf7stilf0mqp1979u8wy04wm9 |title=Mina completes €30M Everton move as Barcelona team-mate Gomes joins|work=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|access-date= 8 August 2018 |date=8 August 2018}}</ref>

His first appearance came during a 3–1 home victory against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], as a last-minute substitute for [[Gylfi Sigurðsson]].

He scored his first goal for Everton in a 5–1 away win against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], a header during the opening two minutes of the match following a cross from [[Bernard (footballer)|Bernard]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46615195 |title=Mina's first Everton goal |publisher= BBC Sport |access-date= 26 December 2018 |date=26 December 2018}}</ref>

He scored his first [[Brace (sports)|brace]] for Everton on 1 February 2020 against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] at [[Vicarage Road]], scoring them both in stoppage time at the end of the first half in a game that Everton came from 2–0 down to win 3–2.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51246503 |title=Watford 2-3 Everton |publisher= BBC Sport |access-date= 1 February 2020 |date=1 February 2020}}</ref>

Mina opened his scoring account for Everton in the 2020–21 season with a bullet header against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton]] in a 4–2 victory at Goodison Park on 3 October 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Calvert-Lewin scores again as Everton go top with win over Brighton |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54305845 |access-date=3 October 2020 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 October 2020}}</ref>

In May 2023, Mina announced that Everton's final game of the [[2022–23 Premier League]] campaign against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] would also be his last game for the club, as he would depart upon the end of the season when his contact expired.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bradbury |first=Sean |date=27 May 2023 |title=Yerry Mina confirms he is leaving Everton and sends heartfelt 'invitation' to fans |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/yerry-mina-leaving-everton-breaking-27008181.amp |url-status=bot: unknown |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251222231148/https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/yerry-mina-leaving-everton-breaking-27008181.amp |archive-date=22 December 2025 |access-date=12 December 2025 |website=Liverpool Echo }}</ref>

===Fiorentina===
On 4 August 2023, Mina moved to Italy and joined [[Serie A]] club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Yerry Mina is a Viola |url=https://www.acffiorentina.com/en/news/all/news-men-first-team/2023-08-04/yerry-mina-is-a-viola |work=ACF Fiorentina |access-date=11 August 2023 |date=4 August 2023 |archive-date=10 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230810200648/https://www.acffiorentina.com/en/news/all/news-men-first-team/2023-08-04/yerry-mina-is-a-viola |url-status=dead }}</ref> He went on to make 4 appearances for the club before subsequently leaving halfway through the [[2023–24 Serie A|season]].

===Cagliari===
On 1 February 2024, Mina signed a contract with [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] until 30 June 2024, with a club's option to extend for the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Cagliari|url=https://www.cagliaricalcio.com/news/ultimissime/23581/yerri-mina-e-del-cagliari-il-difensore-arriva-a-titolo-definitivo|title=Yerri Mina è del Cagliari|trans-title=Yerri Mina is at Cagliari|date=|access-date=1 February 2024|language=it|archive-date=1 February 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240201154904/https://www.cagliaricalcio.com/news/ultimissime/23581/yerri-mina-e-del-cagliari-il-difensore-arriva-a-titolo-definitivo|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:FWC 2018 - Round of 16 - COL v ENG - Photo 048.jpg|thumb|left|Mina ties the match against England in the Round of 16 at the 2018 FIFA World Cup]]
In 2016, Mina was named to Colombia's [[Copa América Centenario]] squad, starting one game against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]]. He played in five of Colombia's [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2018 World Cup Qualifying]] matches from October 2016 to March 2017,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/player/196901/yerry-mina?season=2015 |title=Yerry Mina: Appearances |publisher=ESPNFC}}</ref> and in May 2018 he was named to Colombia's final 23-man [[Colombia national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 World Cup]] in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced? - Goal.com }}</ref>

At the [[2018 World Cup]], Mina scored three goals for Colombia, all of which were headers. Mina did not play in Colombia's opening 2–1 loss against [[Japan national football team|Japan]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331550/#match-liveblog |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612141759/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331550/#match-liveblog |url-status=dead |archive-date=12 June 2018 |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia - Matches - Colombia - Japan |last=FIFA.com |website=www.fifa.com |language=en-GB|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/jun/19/colombia-v-japan-world-cup-2018-live-updates |title=Colombia 1–2 Japan: World Cup 2018 – as it happened |last=Murray |first=Scott |date=19 June 2018 |work=The Guardian|access-date=28 June 2018 |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> but started at [[centre back]] in each of Colombia's remaining matches. In the group stage, he scored the opening goal in a 3–0 win over [[Poland national football team|Poland]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331508/#match-liveblog |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140403/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331508/#match-liveblog |url-status=dead |archive-date=12 June 2018 |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia - Matches - Poland - Colombia |last=FIFA.com |website=www.fifa.com |language=en-GB|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref> then scored the lone goal in a 1–0 win over [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] which propelled Colombia to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup Group H|top of their group]] and into the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|knockout stage]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44439305 |title=World Cup 2018: Senegal 0–1 Colombia |date=28 June 2018 |work=BBC Sport|access-date=28 June 2018 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331553/#match-summary |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143414/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331553/#match-summary |url-status=dead |archive-date=12 June 2018 |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia - Matches - Senegal - Colombia |last=FIFA.com |website=www.fifa.com |language=en-GB|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref> Against [[England national football team|England]] in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|round of sixteen]], Mina tied the scoring 1–1 in the 93rd minute to send the game into extra time. Colombia went on to lose the game on penalty kicks, ending their tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331542/#match-summary |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628233942/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331542/#match-summary |url-status=dead |archive-date=28 June 2018 |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia - Matches - Colombia - England |last=FIFA.com |website=www.fifa.com |language=en-GB|access-date=3 July 2018}}</ref> With his three goals, he tied the record number of goals scored by a defender in a single World Cup tournament, sharing the record with Germans [[Paul Breitner]] in 1974 and [[Andreas Brehme]] in 1990.

==Personal life==
Mina's father and uncle were both professional football [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeepers]]. His father advised him to play another position, and his uncle took him to [[Deportivo Pasto]]'s trial.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.tifofootball.com/features/yerry-minas-journey-colombia-barcelona-via-brazil/ |title=Yerry Mina's journey from Colombia to Barcelona, via Brazil – Tifo Football |work=Tifo Football |access-date=10 January 2018 |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110174312/https://www.tifofootball.com/features/yerry-minas-journey-colombia-barcelona-via-brazil/ |archive-date=10 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> His brother, [[Juan José Mina|Juan José]], is also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasrcn.com/deportes/yerry-mina-juan-jose-mina-hermano-de-yerry-debuto-con-el-cali-418553|title=Hermano de Yerry Mina, sigue los pasos del defensa central y debutó en el fútbol colombiano|trans-title=Brother of Yerry Mina, he follows in the footsteps of the central defender and made his debut in Colombian soccer|date=7 May 2022|accessdate=5 January 2023|website=noticiasrcn.com|language=Spanish}}</ref>

His uncle, Jair Mina, is also his agent.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2749039-yerry-minas-agent-reveals-no-contact-from-barcelona-amid-january-rumours |title=Yerry Mina's Agent Reveals No Contact from Barcelona Amid January Rumours |last=Jones |first=Matt |work=Bleacher Report|access-date=10 January 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>

Mina is a devout [[Christianity|Christian]] and is a member of the neo-Pentecostal [[Church of God Ministry of Jesus Christ International]]. Mina has spoken publicly at many events sponsored by the church to talk about his life and faith.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yerry Mina, el defensa goleador que hizo gritar a Colombia|url=https://www.vanguardia.com/deportes/mundial-de-futbol/yerry-mina-el-defensa-goleador-que-hizo-gritar-a-colombia-JEVL438274|date=8 July 2018|access-date=9 February 2019|language=es|publisher=[[Vanguardia Liberal]]}}</ref>

